at suggests otherwise. It feels a bit cautious, but I think it's reasonable. Making sure I’m not jumping to conclusions is important. Just waiting for more info seems like the prudent choice!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Gathering test setup guidance**\\n\\nI should note that the test setup guidance suggests avoiding the removed classic TypedActor API, which isn't just something normal but is actually useful. I need to focus on collecting documentation to confirm that only the scala-library and config are needed as dependencies. It seems the documentation shows actor and typed dependencies are separate, maybe I’ll use curl docs to help fetch the current docs dependencies page. This could solidify my summary.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_rPGVRetXEQSHBzTiarF94gD4|fc_08aa6e2243f59b45016a406de2c5dc8195bdd453b90112bd1d", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "python3 - <<'PY'\nimport urllib.request,re\nurls=['https://pekko.apache.org/docs/pekko/current/project/quick-start.html','https://pekko.apache.org/docs/pekko/current/actors.html','https://pekko.apache.org/docs/pekko/current/typed/guide/tutorial.html']\nfor url in urls:\n try: s=urllib.request.urlopen(url,timeout=20).read().decode('utf-8','replace')\n except Exception as e: print('ERR',url,e); continue\n print('\\nURL',url,'len',len(s))\n for pat in ['pekko-actor_2.13','pekko-actor-typed_2.13','ActorSystem','Config']:\n  i=s.find(pat)\n  if i>=0: print(pat, re.sub('<[^>]+>',' ',s[max(0,i-250):i+300]).replace('\\n',' ')[:700])\nPY", "timeout": 60}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 723, "output": 1055, "cacheRead": 19968, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 21746, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1782607319573, "responseId": "resp_08aa6e2243f59b45016a406dd80bac8195bf49e88c83a6ca74"}}
